Name: SumOfTwoSquare
Title: Numbers equal to the sum of two square numbers
Author: Laurent Thery
Institution: INRIA Sophia-Antipolis
Date: 13/12/2004
Description:  A proof that a number n can be written as the
sum of two square numbers if and only if each prime factor p of n
that is equal to 3 modulo 4 has its exponent in the decomposition of n
that is even.
Keywords: number theory
Require:
Version: 8.0
